    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"310045\">@Eric Wieser</span>  do you have any suggestions?</p>",
        "id": 513322436,
        "sender_full_name": "Jeremy Tan",
        "timestamp": 1745197170
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"310045\">Eric Wieser</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113488-general/topic/Panic.20in.20rw.3A.20Nat.2Epow.20exponent.20is.20too.20big/near/431518317\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Defining a <code>Mathlib.Nat</code> that is a copy of <code>Nat</code> would fix all this, right? Because whatever strange special casing that is going on would presumably not apply here?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>We could do this, but without actually doing a global replace</p>",
        "id": 513342655,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1745211789
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That is, have a <code>SafeNat</code> type that we copy all the Nat instances to, and some Equivs / induction principles to transport back and forth</p>",
        "id": 513342708,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1745211840
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This would be a leaf file in mathlib with a module doc summarizing this thread</p>",
        "id": 513342773,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1745211863
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe we need a mechanism temporarily marking some functions/expressions as irreducible, like <code>Hold</code> in Mathematica</p>",
